The paper presents an algorithm for computing a maximum agreement subtree of two unrooted evolutionary trees, which involves techniques from graph theory and combinatorics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves optimization problems and graph matching, which are relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-categories.
